name: phosphonate-transporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + phosphonateout = ADP + phosphate + phosphonatein [RN:R00086]
comment: ABC-type (ATP-binding cassette-type) ATPase, characterized by the presence of two similar ATP-binding domains. Does not undergo phosphorylation during the transport process. A bacterial enzyme that imports phosphonate and organophosphate anions.

references.title: Molecular genetic studies of a 10.9-kb operon in Escherichia coli for phosphonate uptake and biodegradation.
